---
const installCommand = 'curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/owainlewis/neo/main/install.sh | bash';
---

<div class="neo-home">
  <section class="neo-hero" aria-labelledby="neo-title">
    <div class="neo-hero-glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="neo-hero-copy">
      <p class="neo-kicker"><span></span> Open source. Built for the terminal.</p>
      <h1 id="neo-title">The coding agent you can <em>trust with the repo.</em></h1>
      <p class="neo-hero-lede">
        Neo turns engineering work into a visible workflow. It plans the work, delegates bounded
        subagents, asks before risky changes, and shows you the evidence.
      </p>
      <div class="neo-actions">
        <a class="neo-button neo-button-primary" href="/docs/install/">
          Install Neo
          <svg viewBox="0 0 20 20" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 10h11m-4-4 4 4-4 4"></path></svg>
        </a>
        <a class="neo-button neo-button-secondary" href="https://github.com/owainlewis/neo">
          View source
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="neo-install" role="group" aria-label="Install command">
        <span aria-hidden="true">$</span>
        <code>{installCommand}</code>
        <button type="button" data-copy-install data-command={installCommand} aria-label="Copy install command">
          <svg class="copy-icon" viewBox="0 0 20 20" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="6" y="6" width="10" height="10" rx="2"></rect><path d="M13 6V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2H5a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v6a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h1"></path></svg>
          <svg class="check-icon" viewBox="0 0 20 20" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m4 10 4 4 8-9"></path></svg>
        </button>
      </div>
      <ul class="neo-proof-list" aria-label="Product facts">
        <li><span>01</span> Single Go binary</li>
        <li><span>02</span> Multi-provider</li>
        <li><span>03</span> Local sessions</li>
        <li><span>04</span> No telemetry</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="neo-workflow-shell" role="group" aria-label="Example Neo workflow">
      <div class="neo-window-bar">
        <div class="neo-window-dots" aria-hidden="true"><i></i><i></i><i></i></div>
        <span>neo · payments-api</span>
        <span class="neo-window-secure"><i></i> trusted</span>
      </div>
      <div class="neo-terminal">
        <div class="neo-prompt-line"><b>›</b> Harden webhook verification and prove it works</div>
        <div class="neo-plan-header">
          <div>
            <span class="neo-terminal-label">WORKFLOW</span>
            <strong>Webhook hardening</strong>
          </div>
          <span class="neo-plan-count">3 / 4</span>
        </div>
        <ol class="neo-task-list">
          <li class="done">
            <span class="neo-task-status">✓</span>
            <div><strong>Trace the request path</strong><small>Read 8 files · 12s</small></div>
          </li>
          <li class="done">
            <span class="neo-task-status">✓</span>
            <div><strong>Implement signature validation</strong><small>Edited 3 files · 48s</small></div>
          </li>
          <li class="active">
            <span class="neo-task-status"><i></i></span>
            <div>
              <strong>Test failure modes</strong><small>Running go test ./internal/webhook/...</small>
              <div class="neo-agent-row">
                <span>└─</span><b>agent / review</b><span>checking replay protection</span><em>7s</em>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="neo-task-status">○</span>
            <div><strong>Review the final diff</strong><small>Waiting on tests</small></div>
          </li>
        </ol>
        <div class="neo-command-result">
          <span class="neo-result-mark">✓</span>
          <code>ok github.com/acme/payments/internal/webhook</code>
          <span>0.84s</span>
        </div>
        <div class="neo-terminal-footer">
          <span><i></i> working</span>
          <span>3 agents · 2m 14s</span>
          <span>claude-opus-4-8</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="neo-statement" aria-labelledby="statement-title">
    <p class="neo-section-number">01 / THE DIFFERENCE</p>
    <h2 id="statement-title">Most agents show you an answer.<br />Neo shows you <em>the work.</em></h2>
    <p>
      Serious engineering is not a magic prompt. It is a sequence of decisions, changes, checks,
      and review. Neo makes that sequence visible while it happens.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="neo-pillars" aria-label="Neo principles">
    <article>
      <div class="neo-pillar-top"><span>01</span><i class="signal-icon" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
      <h3>Workflow-native</h3>
      <p>A live checklist keeps long tasks legible. Every step has a state, activity, and result.</p>
      <div class="neo-mini-plan" aria-hidden="true">
        <span class="complete">✓ Inspect</span><span class="running">● Implement</span><span>○ Verify</span>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article>
      <div class="neo-pillar-top"><span>02</span><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 3 5 6v5c0 4.6 2.8 8 7 10 4.2-2 7-5.4 7-10V6l-7-3Z"></path><path d="m9 12 2 2 4-5"></path></svg></div>
      <h3>Trust is a feature</h3>
      <p>Choose ask, trusted, or read-only mode. Ask mode previews file changes; built-in file tools stay inside the workspace.</p>
      <div class="neo-permission" aria-hidden="true"><span>write_file</span><b>Preview change?</b><i>y / n</i></div>
    </article>
    <article>
      <div class="neo-pillar-top"><span>03</span><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M7 7h10v10H7z"></path><path d="M3 12h4m10 0h4M12 3v4m0 10v4"></path></svg></div>
      <h3>Model-independent</h3>
      <p>Use Anthropic, OpenAI, OpenRouter, or Gemini. Your workflow should outlive any one model.</p>
      <div class="neo-models" aria-hidden="true"><span>Anthropic</span><span>OpenAI</span><span>Gemini</span><span>OpenRouter</span></div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="neo-orchestration" aria-labelledby="orchestration-title">
    <div class="neo-orchestration-copy">
      <p class="neo-section-number">02 / ORCHESTRATION</p>
      <h2 id="orchestration-title">One clear plan.<br /><em>Focused agents.</em></h2>
      <p>
        Neo can delegate bounded pieces of work to fresh subagents, watch their activity live,
        and bring their results back into the main workflow. The coordinator stays accountable
        for the outcome.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><span>✓</span> Separate context for every worker</li>
        <li><span>✓</span> Bounded depth, fan-out, and runtime</li>
        <li><span>✓</span> Live tree of agent activity</li>
        <li><span>✓</span> Results return to the coordinator</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="neo-orbit" role="img" aria-label="Neo coordinator delegating to three subagents">
      <div class="neo-orbit-grid" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="neo-connector connector-a" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="neo-connector connector-b" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="neo-connector connector-c" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="neo-coordinator"><span>NEO</span><b>coordinator</b><i></i></div>
      <div class="neo-worker worker-a"><span>01</span><b>research</b><small>done · 14s</small></div>
      <div class="neo-worker worker-b"><span>02</span><b>implement</b><small>working · 38s</small></div>
      <div class="neo-worker worker-c"><span>03</span><b>review</b><small>queued</small></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="neo-comparison" aria-labelledby="comparison-title">
    <div class="neo-comparison-heading">
      <p class="neo-section-number">03 / BUILT FOR ENGINEERS</p>
      <h2 id="comparison-title">Less theatre.<br /><em>More evidence.</em></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="neo-comparison-grid">
      <div class="neo-not-this">
        <span class="neo-comparison-label">The black box</span>
        <ul>
          <li><span>×</span> Hidden execution state</li>
          <li><span>×</span> One model, one vendor</li>
          <li><span>×</span> Unclear permission boundaries</li>
          <li><span>×</span> “Done” without proof</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="neo-this">
        <span class="neo-comparison-label">The Neo harness</span>
        <ul>
          <li><span>✓</span> Live workflow and tool activity</li>
          <li><span>✓</span> Multiple providers, one workflow</li>
          <li><span>✓</span> Explicit permissions and previews</li>
          <li><span>✓</span> Tests, diffs, and visible results</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="neo-foundation" aria-labelledby="foundation-title">
    <p class="neo-section-number">04 / THE FOUNDATION</p>
    <h2 id="foundation-title">Small core.<br /><em>Serious capability.</em></h2>
    <div class="neo-foundation-grid">
      <div><strong>01</strong><h3>One binary</h3><p>No runtime to assemble. Install it and work.</p></div>
      <div><strong>02</strong><h3>Local-first</h3><p>Sessions stay local. Project context goes to the model provider you choose.</p></div>
      <div><strong>03</strong><h3>Open source</h3><p>Inspect the harness you are trusting with your code.</p></div>
      <div><strong>04</strong><h3>Policy-free core</h3><p>A small agent loop with capabilities layered around it.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="neo-final-cta" aria-labelledby="cta-title">
    <div class="neo-cta-grid" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <p class="neo-kicker"><span></span> Your repo. Your models. Your workflow.</p>
    <h2 id="cta-title">Put the work<br /><em>in the open.</em></h2>
    <p>Install Neo and give your next coding task a workflow you can actually follow.</p>
    <div class="neo-actions">
      <a class="neo-button neo-button-primary" href="/docs/install/">Install Neo</a>
      <a class="neo-button neo-button-secondary" href="/docs/quick-start/">Read the docs</a>
    </div>
    <code class="neo-final-command">$ {installCommand}</code>
  </section>
</div>

<script>
  const button = document.querySelector('[data-copy-install]');

  const copyText = async (text: string) => {
    try {
      await navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
      return true;
    } catch {
      const input = document.createElement('textarea');
      input.value = text;
      input.setAttribute('readonly', '');
      input.style.position = 'fixed';
      input.style.opacity = '0';
      document.body.append(input);
      input.select();
      const copied = document.execCommand('copy');
      input.remove();
      return copied;
    }
  };

  button?.addEventListener('click', async () => {
    const command = button.getAttribute('data-command') ?? '';
    if (await copyText(command)) {
      button.classList.add('copied');
      button.setAttribute('aria-label', 'Install command copied');
      window.setTimeout(() => {
        button.classList.remove('copied');
        button.setAttribute('aria-label', 'Copy install command');
      }, 1800);
    } else {
      button.setAttribute('aria-label', 'Copy failed. Select the command manually.');
    }
  });
</script>
